From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Sat, 14 Feb 2026 14:19:49 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] Docs/mm/damon/design: document the power-of-two limitation
 for addr_unit

Update documentation to clarify the limitation on addr_unit, that made
via commit c80f46ac228b ("mm/damon/core: disallow non-power of two
min_region_sz").

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 Documentation/mm/damon/design.rst | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Documentation/mm/damon/design.rst b/Documentation/mm/damon/design.rst
index 28d932ceaf7ed..3896dde76e709 100644
--- a/Documentation/mm/damon/design.rst
+++ b/Documentation/mm/damon/design.rst
@@ -150,6 +150,8 @@ address on the given address space.  Support of ``address unit`` parameter is
 up to each operations set implementation.  ``paddr`` is the only operations set
 implementation that supports the parameter.
 
+If the value is lower than 4096, only a power of two value should be used.
+
 .. _damon_core_logic:
 
 Core Logics
-- 
2.47.3

